Preserved tadpoles have translucent pale brown skin, clearer in tail. Dorsum with sparse dark-brown spots, the golden color became a clear bare visible brown. Black bars and blotches became dark brown. Intestine remains visible. Iris black. Tadpoles (
UFBA
10750
) in earlier (
25–27
) and later (
40–41
) stages are congruent with respect to general morphology and color of tadpoles in stages 
31–38
.

